# Pork Salad w Noodles

> This #salad recipe mixes hot & cold for some refreshing herbal emotions

## Dressing

- Lemons | 1 tsp zest |
- Limes | 1 count | Juice
- Orange Juice | 2 tbsp | 
- Fish Sauce | 2 tbsp | 
- Honey | 1 tbsp | 
- Salt | to taste | 

Whisk together

## Salad Bowl

- Vegetable Oil | 3 tbsp | 
- Green Onions | 1 count |

Whisk in large bowl with half above dressing

- Pad Thai (Flat) Noodle | 6 oz | 

Cook according to package

Add to larger bowl

## Noodles & Meat

- Vegetable Oil | 1 tbsp | 
- Garlic | 2 cloves | Mashed to paste
- Ginger Root | 2 inches | Peeled & Grated
- Thai Chili | (opt) 1 count |

Cook in pan, about 1 minute

- Ground Pork | 1 lb | 

Cook w/ minimal stirring, keep pork in bite sized chunks, about 8 minutes

Glaze w/ smaller (non-shallot/noodles) mixture, until thick

## Salad

- Cucumber | 1 cup | Thinly sliced
- Green Onions | 2 count | Separate white/green
- Cherry Tomatoes | 1.25 cups | Halved
- Bean Sprout | 1 cup |
- Mint | 1 cup (packed) |
- Basil Leaves | 1 cup | 
- Romaine | 2 cups (or 3 w/o Mung) | 

Combine all but hot ingredients

- Red Pepper Flakes | To taste | 
- Limes | Wedges, for serving |

Serve individual plates w/ hot ingredients, garnish to taste

